An Act relative to Title 5 of the State Environmental Code.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Pursuant to 310 CMR 15.000, the department shall not require a dwelling
2 used as a primary residence to install or upgrade to Best Available Nitrogen Reducing
3 Technology, unless said installation or upgrade is required by an enforceable Watershed Permit
4 issued pursuant to 314 CMR 21.00. No Watershed Permit shall be required or enforced unless
5 the department or the general court, by appropriation, provides for any cost obligations imposed
6 upon the Local Government Unit, including any costs incurred to a primary residence.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon its passage.
